199#else
200#define XM_FMADD_PS( a, b, c ) _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps((a), (b)), (c))
201#define XM_FNMADD_PS( a, b, c ) _mm_sub_ps((c), _mm_mul_ps((a), (b)))

208#endif

263 constexpr float XM_PI = 3.141592654f;
264 constexpr float XM_2PI = 6.283185307f;
265 constexpr float XM_1DIVPI = 0.318309886f;
266 constexpr float XM_1DIV2PI = 0.159154943f;
267 constexpr float XM_PIDIV2 = 1.570796327f;
268 constexpr float XM_PIDIV4 = 0.785398163f;
269
270 constexpr uint32_t XM_SELECT_0 = 0x00000000;
271 constexpr uint32_t XM_SELECT_1 = 0xFFFFFFFF;
272
273 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_0X = 0;
274 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_0Y = 1;
275 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_0Z = 2;
276 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_0W = 3;
277 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_1X = 4;
278 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_1Y = 5;
279 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_1Z = 6;
280 constexpr uint32_t XM_PERMUTE_1W = 7;
281
282 constexpr uint32_t XM_SWIZZLE_X = 0;
283 constexpr uint32_t XM_SWIZZLE_Y = 1;
284 constexpr uint32_t XM_SWIZZLE_Z = 2;
285 constexpr uint32_t XM_SWIZZLE_W = 3;
286
287 constexpr uint32_t XM_CRMASK_CR6 = 0x000000F0;
288 constexpr uint32_t XM_CRMASK_CR6TRUE = 0x00000080;
289 constexpr uint32_t XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE = 0x00000020;
290 constexpr uint32_t XM_CRMASK_CR6BOUNDS = XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE;
291
292#if defined(_M_ARM) || defined(_M_ARM64) || defined(_M_HYBRID_X86_ARM64) || defined(_M_ARM64EC) || __arm__ || __aarch64__

307#undef XMComparisonAnyTrue

311#undef XMComparisonAllInBounds
312#undef XMComparisonAnyOutOfBounds

315 // Unit conversion
316
317 constexpr float XMConvertToRadians(float fDegrees) noexcept { return fDegrees * (XM_PI / 180.0f); }
318 constexpr float XMConvertToDegrees(float fRadians) noexcept { return fRadians * (180.0f / XM_PI); }
319
320 // Condition register evaluation proceeding a recording (R) comparison
321
322 constexpr bool XMComparisonAllTrue(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6TRUE) == XM_CRMASK_CR6TRUE; }
323 constexpr bool XMComparisonAnyTrue(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE) != XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE; }
324 constexpr bool XMComparisonAllFalse(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE) == XM_CRMASK_CR6FALSE; }
325 constexpr bool XMComparisonAnyFalse(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6TRUE) != XM_CRMASK_CR6TRUE; }
326 constexpr bool XMComparisonMixed(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6) == 0; }
327 constexpr bool XMComparisonAllInBounds(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6BOUNDS) == XM_CRMASK_CR6BOUNDS; }
328 constexpr bool XMComparisonAnyOutOfBounds(uint32_t CR) noexcept { return (CR & XM_CRMASK_CR6BOUNDS) != XM_CRMASK_CR6BOUNDS; }

363 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
364 // Vector intrinsic: Four 32 bit floating point components aligned on a 16 byte
365 // boundary and mapped to hardware vector registers
366#if defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
367 using XMVECTOR = __m128;
368#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
369 using XMVECTOR = float32x4_t;
370#else
371 using XMVECTOR = __vector4;
372#endif
373
374 // Fix-up for (1st-3rd) XMVECTOR parameters that are pass-in-register for x86, ARM, ARM64, and vector call; by reference otherwise
375#if ( defined(_M_IX86) || defined(_M_ARM) || defined(_M_ARM64) || _XM_VECTORCALL_ || __i386__ || __arm__ || __aarch64__ ) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
376 typedef const XMVECTOR FXMVECTOR;
377#else
378 typedef const XMVECTOR& FXMVECTOR;
379#endif
380
381 // Fix-up for (4th) XMVECTOR parameter to pass in-register for ARM, ARM64, and vector call; by reference otherwise
382#if ( defined(_M_ARM) || defined(_M_ARM64) || defined(_M_HYBRID_X86_ARM64) || defined(_M_ARM64EC) || _XM_VECTORCALL_ || __arm__ || __aarch64__ ) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
383 typedef const XMVECTOR GXMVECTOR;
384#else
385 typedef const XMVECTOR& GXMVECTOR;
386#endif
387
388 // Fix-up for (5th & 6th) XMVECTOR parameter to pass in-register for ARM64 and vector call; by reference otherwise
389#if ( defined(_M_ARM64) || defined(_M_HYBRID_X86_ARM64) || defined(_M_ARM64EC) || _XM_VECTORCALL_ || __aarch64__ ) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
390 typedef const XMVECTOR HXMVECTOR;
391#else
392 typedef const XMVECTOR& HXMVECTOR;
393#endif
394
395 // Fix-up for (7th+) XMVECTOR parameters to pass by reference
396 typedef const XMVECTOR& CXMVECTOR;

398 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
399 // Conversion types for constants
400 XM_ALIGNED_STRUCT(16) XMVECTORF32
401 {
402 union
403 {
404 float f[4];
405 XMVECTOR v;
406 };
407
408 inline operator XMVECTOR() const noexcept { return v; }
409 inline operator const float* () const noexcept { return f; }
410#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
411#elif defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_)
412 inline operator __m128i() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_si128(v); }
413 inline operator __m128d() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_pd(v); }
414#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_) && (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(_ARM64_DISTINCT_NEON_TYPES))
415 inline operator int32x4_t() const noexcept { return vreinterpretq_s32_f32(v); }
416 inline operator uint32x4_t() const noexcept { return vreinterpretq_u32_f32(v); }
417#endif
418 };
419
420 XM_ALIGNED_STRUCT(16) XMVECTORI32
421 {
422 union
423 {
424 int32_t i[4];
425 XMVECTOR v;
426 };
427
428 inline operator XMVECTOR() const noexcept { return v; }
429#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
430#elif defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_)
431 inline operator __m128i() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_si128(v); }
432 inline operator __m128d() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_pd(v); }
433#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_) && (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(_ARM64_DISTINCT_NEON_TYPES))
434 inline operator int32x4_t() const noexcept { return vreinterpretq_s32_f32(v); }
435 inline operator uint32x4_t() const noexcept { return vreinterpretq_u32_f32(v); }
436#endif
437 };
438

440 {
441 union
442 {
443 uint8_t u[16];
444 XMVECTOR v;
445 };
446
447 inline operator XMVECTOR() const noexcept { return v; }
448#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
449#elif defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_)
450 inline operator __m128i() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_si128(v); }
451 inline operator __m128d() const noexcept { return _mm_castps_pd(v); }
452#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_) && (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(_ARM64_DISTINCT_NEON_TYPES))
453 inline operator int32x4_t() const noexcept { return vreinterpretq_s32_f32(v); }

501 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
502 // Matrix type: Sixteen 32 bit floating point components aligned on a
503 // 16 byte boundary and mapped to four hardware vector registers
504
505 struct XMMATRIX;
506
507 // Fix-up for (1st) XMMATRIX parameter to pass in-register for ARM64 and vector call; by reference otherwise
508#if ( defined(_M_ARM64) || defined(_M_HYBRID_X86_ARM64) || defined(_M_ARM64EC) || _XM_VECTORCALL_ || __aarch64__ ) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
509 typedef const XMMATRIX FXMMATRIX;
510#else
511 typedef const XMMATRIX& FXMMATRIX;
512#endif
513
514 // Fix-up for (2nd+) XMMATRIX parameters to pass by reference
515 typedef const XMMATRIX& CXMMATRIX;
516
517#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
518 struct XMMATRIX
519#else
520 XM_ALIGNED_STRUCT(16) XMMATRIX
521#endif
522 {
523#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
524 union
525 {
526 XMVECTOR r[4];
527 struct
528 {
529 float _11, _12, _13, _14;
530 float _21, _22, _23, _24;
531 float _31, _32, _33, _34;
532 float _41, _42, _43, _44;
533 };
534 float m[4][4];
535 };
536#else
537 XMVECTOR r[4];
538#endif
539
540 XMMATRIX() = default;
541
542 XMMATRIX(const XMMATRIX&) = default;
543
544#if defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_FULL_VER < 191426431)
545 XMMATRIX& operator= (const XMMATRIX& M) noexcept { r[0] = M.r[0]; r[1] = M.r[1]; r[2] = M.r[2]; r[3] = M.r[3]; return *this; }
546#else
547 XMMATRIX& operator=(const XMMATRIX&) = default;
548
549 XMMATRIX(XMMATRIX&&) = default;
550 XMMATRIX& operator=(XMMATRIX&&) = default;
551#endif
552
553 constexpr XMMATRIX(FXMVECTOR R0, FXMVECTOR R1, FXMVECTOR R2, CXMVECTOR R3) noexcept : r{ R0,R1,R2,R3 } {}
554 XMMATRIX(float m00, float m01, float m02, float m03,
555 float m10, float m11, float m12, float m13,
556 float m20, float m21, float m22, float m23,
557 float m30, float m31, float m32, float m33) noexcept;
558 explicit XMMATRIX(_In_reads_(16) const float* pArray) noexcept;
559
560#ifdef _XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
561 float operator() (size_t Row, size_t Column) const noexcept { return m[Row][Column]; }
562 float& operator() (size_t Row, size_t Column) noexcept { return m[Row][Column]; }
563#endif
564
565 XMMATRIX operator+ () const noexcept { return *this; }
566 XMMATRIX operator- () const noexcept;
567
568 XMMATRIX& XM_CALLCONV operator+= (FXMMATRIX M) noexcept;
569 XMMATRIX& XM_CALLCONV operator-= (FXMMATRIX M) noexcept;
570 XMMATRIX& XM_CALLCONV operator*= (FXMMATRIX M) noexcept;
571 XMMATRIX& operator*= (float S) noexcept;
572 XMMATRIX& operator/= (float S) noexcept;
573
574 XMMATRIX XM_CALLCONV operator+ (FXMMATRIX M) const noexcept;
575 XMMATRIX XM_CALLCONV operator- (FXMMATRIX M) const noexcept;
576 XMMATRIX XM_CALLCONV operator* (FXMMATRIX M) const noexcept;
577 XMMATRIX operator* (float S) const noexcept;
578 XMMATRIX operator/ (float S) const noexcept;
579
580 friend XMMATRIX XM_CALLCONV operator* (float S, FXMMATRIX M) noexcept;
581 };
582

837 };

850 : _11(m00), _12(m01), _13(m02),

1713 /****************************************************************************
1714 *
1715 * Templates
1716 *

1718
1719#if defined(__XNAMATH_H__) && defined(XMMin)
1720#undef XMMin
1721#undef XMMax
1722#endif
1723
1724 template<class T> inline T XMMin(T a, T b) noexcept { return (a < b) ? a : b; }
1725 template<class T> inline T XMMax(T a, T b) noexcept { return (a > b) ? a : b; }

1727 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1728
1729#if defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
1730
1731// PermuteHelper internal template (SSE only)
1732 namespace Internal
1733 {
1734 // Slow path fallback for permutes that do not map to a single SSE shuffle opcode.
1735 template<uint32_t Shuffle, bool WhichX, bool WhichY, bool WhichZ, bool WhichW> struct PermuteHelper
1736 {
1737 static XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV Permute(FXMVECTOR v1, FXMVECTOR v2) noexcept
1738 {
1739 static const XMVECTORU32 selectMask =
1740 { { {
1741 WhichX ? 0xFFFFFFFF : 0,
1742 WhichY ? 0xFFFFFFFF : 0,
1743 WhichZ ? 0xFFFFFFFF : 0,
1744 WhichW ? 0xFFFFFFFF : 0,
1745 } } };
1746
1747 XMVECTOR shuffled1 = XM_PERMUTE_PS(v1, Shuffle);
1748 XMVECTOR shuffled2 = XM_PERMUTE_PS(v2, Shuffle);
1749
1750 XMVECTOR masked1 = _mm_andnot_ps(selectMask, shuffled1);
1751 XMVECTOR masked2 = _mm_and_ps(selectMask, shuffled2);
1752
1753 return _mm_or_ps(masked1, masked2);
1754 }
1755 };
1756
1757 // Fast path for permutes that only read from the first vector.
1758 template<uint32_t Shuffle> struct PermuteHelper<Shuffle, false, false, false, false>
1759 {
1760 static XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV Permute(FXMVECTOR v1, FXMVECTOR) noexcept { return XM_PERMUTE_PS(v1, Shuffle); }
1761 };
1762
1763 // Fast path for permutes that only read from the second vector.
1764 template<uint32_t Shuffle> struct PermuteHelper<Shuffle, true, true, true, true>
1765 {
1766 static XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV Permute(FXMVECTOR, FXMVECTOR v2) noexcept { return XM_PERMUTE_PS(v2, Shuffle); }
1767 };
1768
1769 // Fast path for permutes that read XY from the first vector, ZW from the second.
1770 template<uint32_t Shuffle> struct PermuteHelper<Shuffle, false, false, true, true>
1771 {
1772 static XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV Permute(FXMVECTOR v1, FXMVECTOR v2) noexcept { return _mm_shuffle_ps(v1, v2, Shuffle); }
1773 };
1774
1775 // Fast path for permutes that read XY from the second vector, ZW from the first.
1776 template<uint32_t Shuffle> struct PermuteHelper<Shuffle, true, true, false, false>
1777 {
1778 static XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV Permute(FXMVECTOR v1, FXMVECTOR v2) noexcept { return _mm_shuffle_ps(v2, v1, Shuffle); }
1779 };
1780 }
1781
1782#endif // _XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_ && !_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
1783
1784 // General permute template
1785 template<uint32_t PermuteX, uint32_t PermuteY, uint32_t PermuteZ, uint32_t PermuteW>
1786 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorPermute(FXMVECTOR V1, FXMVECTOR V2) noexcept
1787 {
1788 static_assert(PermuteX <= 7, "PermuteX template parameter out of range");
1789 static_assert(PermuteY <= 7, "PermuteY template parameter out of range");
1790 static_assert(PermuteZ <= 7, "PermuteZ template parameter out of range");
1791 static_assert(PermuteW <= 7, "PermuteW template parameter out of range");
1792
1793#if defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
1794 constexpr uint32_t Shuffle = _MM_SHUFFLE(PermuteW & 3, PermuteZ & 3, PermuteY & 3, PermuteX & 3);
1795
1796 constexpr bool WhichX = PermuteX > 3;
1797 constexpr bool WhichY = PermuteY > 3;
1798 constexpr bool WhichZ = PermuteZ > 3;
1799 constexpr bool WhichW = PermuteW > 3;
1800
1801 return Internal::PermuteHelper<Shuffle, WhichX, WhichY, WhichZ, WhichW>::Permute(V1, V2);
1802#else
1803
1804 return XMVectorPermute(V1, V2, PermuteX, PermuteY, PermuteZ, PermuteW);
1805
1806#endif
1807 }
1808
1809 // Special-case permute templates
1810 template<> constexpr XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorPermute<0, 1, 2, 3>(FXMVECTOR V1, FXMVECTOR) noexcept { return V1; }
1811 template<> constexpr XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorPermute<4, 5, 6, 7>(FXMVECTOR, FXMVECTOR V2) noexcept { return V2; }

1817 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorPermute<2, 6, 3, 7>(FXMVECTOR V1, FXMVECTOR V2) noexcept { return _mm_unpackhi_ps(V1, V2); }

1880 // General swizzle template
1881 template<uint32_t SwizzleX, uint32_t SwizzleY, uint32_t SwizzleZ, uint32_t SwizzleW>
1882 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept
1883 {
1884 static_assert(SwizzleX <= 3, "SwizzleX template parameter out of range");
1885 static_assert(SwizzleY <= 3, "SwizzleY template parameter out of range");
1886 static_assert(SwizzleZ <= 3, "SwizzleZ template parameter out of range");
1887 static_assert(SwizzleW <= 3, "SwizzleW template parameter out of range");
1888
1889#if defined(_XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_) && !defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
1890 return XM_PERMUTE_PS(V, _MM_SHUFFLE(SwizzleW, SwizzleZ, SwizzleY, SwizzleX));
1891#else
1892
1893 return XMVectorSwizzle(V, SwizzleX, SwizzleY, SwizzleZ, SwizzleW);
1894
1895#endif
1896 }

1926 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<0, 1, 0, 1>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { float32x2_t vt = vget_low_f32(V); return vcombine_f32(vt, vt); }
1927 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<2, 3, 2, 3>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { float32x2_t vt = vget_high_f32(V); return vcombine_f32(vt, vt); }
1928 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<1, 0, 1, 0>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { float32x2_t vt = vrev64_f32(vget_low_f32(V)); return vcombine_f32(vt, vt); }
1929 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<3, 2, 3, 2>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { float32x2_t vt = vrev64_f32(vget_high_f32(V)); return vcombine_f32(vt, vt); }
1930
1931 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<0, 1, 3, 2>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vcombine_f32(vget_low_f32(V), vrev64_f32(vget_high_f32(V))); }
1932 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<1, 0, 2, 3>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vcombine_f32(vrev64_f32(vget_low_f32(V)), vget_high_f32(V)); }
1933 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<2, 3, 1, 0>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vcombine_f32(vget_high_f32(V), vrev64_f32(vget_low_f32(V))); }
1934 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<3, 2, 0, 1>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vcombine_f32(vrev64_f32(vget_high_f32(V)), vget_low_f32(V)); }
1935 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<3, 2, 1, 0>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vcombine_f32(vrev64_f32(vget_high_f32(V)), vrev64_f32(vget_low_f32(V))); }
1936
1937 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<0, 0, 2, 2>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vtrnq_f32(V, V).val[0]; }
1938 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<1, 1, 3, 3>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vtrnq_f32(V, V).val[1]; }
1939
1940 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<0, 0, 1, 1>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vzipq_f32(V, V).val[0]; }
1941 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<2, 2, 3, 3>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vzipq_f32(V, V).val[1]; }
1942
1943 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<0, 2, 0, 2>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vuzpq_f32(V, V).val[0]; }
1944 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<1, 3, 1, 3>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vuzpq_f32(V, V).val[1]; }
1945
1946 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<1, 2, 3, 0>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vextq_f32(V, V, 1); }
1947 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<2, 3, 0, 1>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vextq_f32(V, V, 2); }
1948 template<> inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSwizzle<3, 0, 1, 2>(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept { return vextq_f32(V, V, 3); }
1949
1950#endif // _XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_ && !_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_
1951
1952 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1953
1954 template<uint32_t Elements>
1955 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorShiftLeft(FXMVECTOR V1, FXMVECTOR V2) noexcept
1956 {
1957 static_assert(Elements < 4, "Elements template parameter out of range");
1958 return XMVectorPermute<Elements, (Elements + 1), (Elements + 2), (Elements + 3)>(V1, V2);
1959 }
1960
1961 template<uint32_t Elements>
1962 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorRotateLeft(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept
1963 {
1964 static_assert(Elements < 4, "Elements template parameter out of range");
1965 return XMVectorSwizzle<Elements & 3, (Elements + 1) & 3, (Elements + 2) & 3, (Elements + 3) & 3>(V);
1966 }
1967
1968 template<uint32_t Elements>
1969 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorRotateRight(FXMVECTOR V) noexcept
1970 {
1971 static_assert(Elements < 4, "Elements template parameter out of range");
1972 return XMVectorSwizzle<(4 - Elements) & 3, (5 - Elements) & 3, (6 - Elements) & 3, (7 - Elements) & 3>(V);
1973 }
1974
1975 template<uint32_t VSLeftRotateElements, uint32_t Select0, uint32_t Select1, uint32_t Select2, uint32_t Select3>
1976 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorInsert(FXMVECTOR VD, FXMVECTOR VS) noexcept
1977 {
1978 XMVECTOR Control = XMVectorSelectControl(Select0 & 1, Select1 & 1, Select2 & 1, Select3 & 1);
1979 return XMVectorSelect(VD, XMVectorRotateLeft<VSLeftRotateElements>(VS), Control);
1980 }

1982 /****************************************************************************
1983 *
1984 * Globals
1985 *
1986 ****************************************************************************/
1987
1988 // The purpose of the following global constants is to prevent redundant
1989 // reloading of the constants when they are referenced by more than one
1990 // separate inline math routine called within the same function. Declaring
1991 // a constant locally within a routine is sufficient to prevent redundant
1992 // reloads of that constant when that single routine is called multiple
1993 // times in a function, but if the constant is used (and declared) in a
1994 // separate math routine it would be reloaded.
1995
1996#ifndef XMGLOBALCONST
1997#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__MINGW32__)
1998#define XMGLOBALCONST extern const __attribute__((weak))
1999#else
2000#define XMGLOBALCONST extern const __declspec(selectany)
2001#endif
2002#endif
2003

2173//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2174
2175 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSetBinaryConstant(uint32_t C0, uint32_t C1, uint32_t C2, uint32_t C3) noexcept
2176 {
2177#if defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
2178 XMVECTORU32 vResult;
2179 vResult.u[0] = (0 - (C0 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2180 vResult.u[1] = (0 - (C1 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2181 vResult.u[2] = (0 - (C2 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2182 vResult.u[3] = (0 - (C3 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2183 return vResult.v;
2184#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_)
2185 XMVECTORU32 vResult;
2186 vResult.u[0] = (0 - (C0 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2187 vResult.u[1] = (0 - (C1 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2188 vResult.u[2] = (0 - (C2 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2189 vResult.u[3] = (0 - (C3 & 1)) & 0x3F800000;
2190 return vResult.v;
2191#else // XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_
2192 static const XMVECTORU32 g_vMask1 = { { { 1, 1, 1, 1 } } };
2193 // Move the parms to a vector
2194 __m128i vTemp = _mm_set_epi32(static_cast<int>(C3), static_cast<int>(C2), static_cast<int>(C1), static_cast<int>(C0));
2195 // Mask off the low bits
2196 vTemp = _mm_and_si128(vTemp, g_vMask1);
2197 // 0xFFFFFFFF on true bits
2198 vTemp = _mm_cmpeq_epi32(vTemp, g_vMask1);
2199 // 0xFFFFFFFF -> 1.0f, 0x00000000 -> 0.0f
2200 vTemp = _mm_and_si128(vTemp, g_XMOne);
2201 return _mm_castsi128_ps(vTemp);
2202#endif
2203 }
2204
2205 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2206
2207 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSplatConstant(int32_t IntConstant, uint32_t DivExponent) noexcept
2208 {
2209 assert(IntConstant >= -16 && IntConstant <= 15);
2210 assert(DivExponent < 32);
2211#if defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
2212
2213 using DirectX::XMConvertVectorIntToFloat;
2214
2215 XMVECTORI32 V = { { { IntConstant, IntConstant, IntConstant, IntConstant } } };
2216 return XMConvertVectorIntToFloat(V.v, DivExponent);
2217
2218#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_)
2219 // Splat the int
2220 int32x4_t vScale = vdupq_n_s32(IntConstant);
2221 // Convert to a float
2222 XMVECTOR vResult = vcvtq_f32_s32(vScale);
2223 // Convert DivExponent into 1.0f/(1<<DivExponent)
2224 uint32_t uScale = 0x3F800000U - (DivExponent << 23);
2225 // Splat the scalar value (It's really a float)
2226 vScale = vreinterpretq_s32_u32(vdupq_n_u32(uScale));
2227 // Multiply by the reciprocal (Perform a right shift by DivExponent)
2228 vResult = vmulq_f32(vResult, reinterpret_cast<const float32x4_t*>(&vScale)[0]);
2229 return vResult;
2230#else // XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_
2231 // Splat the int
2232 __m128i vScale = _mm_set1_epi32(IntConstant);
2233 // Convert to a float
2234 XMVECTOR vResult = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(vScale);
2235 // Convert DivExponent into 1.0f/(1<<DivExponent)
2236 uint32_t uScale = 0x3F800000U - (DivExponent << 23);
2237 // Splat the scalar value (It's really a float)
2238 vScale = _mm_set1_epi32(static_cast<int>(uScale));
2239 // Multiply by the reciprocal (Perform a right shift by DivExponent)
2240 vResult = _mm_mul_ps(vResult, _mm_castsi128_ps(vScale));
2241 return vResult;
2242#endif
2243 }
2244
2245 //------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2246
2247 inline XMVECTOR XM_CALLCONV XMVectorSplatConstantInt(int32_t IntConstant) noexcept
2248 {
2249 assert(IntConstant >= -16 && IntConstant <= 15);
2250#if defined(_XM_NO_INTRINSICS_)
2251
2252 XMVECTORI32 V = { { { IntConstant, IntConstant, IntConstant, IntConstant } } };
2253 return V.v;
2254
2255#elif defined(_XM_ARM_NEON_INTRINSICS_)
2256 int32x4_t V = vdupq_n_s32(IntConstant);
2257 return reinterpret_cast<float32x4_t*>(&V)[0];
2258#else // XM_SSE_INTRINSICS_
2259 __m128i V = _mm_set1_epi32(IntConstant);
2260 return _mm_castsi128_ps(V);
2261#endif
2262 }
